  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Grifone is on a half board basis.</p>
<p>Start the week off with a free aperitivo, before enjoying a four-course evening meal with a choice of dishes - often including fish, meats and vegetarian dishes. Once a week you will be treated to a Ladino dinner with typical regional dishes served.</p>
<p>Each morning a filling breakfast buffet is served to prepare you for an active day on the slopes.</p>
<p>Christmas and New Year gala meals included.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Grifone has a quiet location near the Campolongo pass. It's a beautifully designed hotel between the resorts <a data-udi="umb://document/3a67ce6017fa4e79a469b4fc75f18150" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3a67ce6017fa4e79a469b4fc75f18150}" title="Arabba">Arabba</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8}" title="Corvara &amp; Colfosco">Corvara</a>, surrounded by the spectacular <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomite</a> mountains. You can be sure of a great holiday here with spacious rooms and mountain views from the balcony.</p>
<h2>Free Shuttle Bus</h2>
<p>For those who want to be the first on the slopes, jump on hotel's free shuttle bus from 8.30am. You'll be taken directly to the Mont Cherz lift, which leads straight onto the Sella Ronda circuit. If you want a relaxing start to the morning the shuttle runs throughout the day, so you can enjoy a lie in and a leisurely breakfast. When its time to return make your way down to the Mont Cherz lift station before 5.30pm and enjoy a scenic journey back to the hotel.</p>
<h2>Wellness Area</h2>
<p>If you fancy an afternoon off from skiing, we highly recommend the hotel's wellness centre. Take a dip in the pool and make the most of the views of the Dolomites, close your eyes and relax in the steam room or turn up the heat in the sauna. If you want to fully relax massages and treatments are available to book through the hotel (pay locally). </p>
<h2>Piano Bar</h2>
<p>The hotel's piano bar really brings the whole place to life both before and after a delicious four-course evening meal. Once a week you can enjoy a typical Ladin style dinner, perfect for sampling some of the tasty regional cuisine. Enjoy a tipple next to the warmth of the open log fire, sit back and chat about the day's events in the comfy leather chairs or join in with the evening entertainment hosted throughout the week.</p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
